# Git operations — GitKraken MCP only

Alan has GitKraken MCP enabled. **Do not use Shell for git writes** (add, commit, push, branch, checkout).

## Use GitKraken MCP (`user-GitKraken`)

| Task | Tool | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| Stage | `git_add_or_commit` action `add` | `directory`: repo root, `files`: `["lib/foo.js"]` |
| Commit | `git_add_or_commit` action `commit` | `message` required; optional `files` for partial commit |
| Push | `git_push` | `directory`: repo root |
| Status / log / diff | `git_status`, `git_log_or_diff` | Read-only; prefer MCP over Shell |

**Repo paths (common):**

- Academy: `G:\Dropbox\alan ranger photography\Website Code\Academy\alanranger-academy-assesment`
- Chat AI Bot: `G:\Dropbox\alan ranger photography\Website Code\Chat AI Bot`
- AI GEO Audit: `G:\Dropbox\alan ranger photography\Website Code\AI GEO Audit`

## Shell git — read-only only

Shell is OK for **inspection** when MCP is awkward: `git status`, `git log`, `git diff`. Never `git commit`, `git push`, `git add` via Shell.

